  "prompt": "What is the weirdest question you have ever been asked in an interview?",
  "response": "While I don\u2019t have personal experiences, I can share some unusual interview questions that candidates have reported. One bizarre question is, \u201cIf you were a pizza delivery person, how would you benefit from scissors?\u201d This type of question is designed to assess creativity and problem-solving skills rather than seek a practical answer. \n\nAnother example is, \u201cIf you could be any animal, what would you be and why?\u201d This can help interviewers gauge a candidate's personality and how they see themselves in different roles. Such questions often aim to see how candidates think on their feet and how they can express their thoughts in an unconventional way.",
